Question 1

“Flowchart 1”

check.integer

This program will allow the user to determine whether an inputted value is an integer

  the function is TRUE if the inputted value is equal to the same value rounded to the nearest integer

  the function is FALSE if the inputted value is not equal to the same value rounded to the nearest integer

gcd

This program will allow the user to find the greatest common divisor of two integers

    IF the value of b is greater than the value of a

      stop running code, and print response 

        "the value of b must be less than or equal to the value of a"
  
  IF a is not an integer

    stop running code, and print response

      "a must be an integer"

  IF b is not an integer

   stop running code, and print response

     "b must be an integer"
  
 set r equal to the remainder of a divided by b

 set r2 equal to a

 set r3 equal to b

  IF r is equal to 0

    print response 

      b
  
   ELSE conduct the following commands

      WHILE r3 does not equal 0
  
        set r1 equal to the remainder of r2 divided by r3
    
        set r2 to r3
    
       set r3 to r1
    
     print response
    
       r2

gcd_3

This program will allow the user to find the greatest common divisor of two integers

  IF the value of b is greater than the value of a

   stop running code, and print response 

     "the value of b must be less than or equal to the value of a"
  
 IF the value of c is greater than the value of a

    stop running code, and print response 

      "the value of c must be less than or equal to the value of a"
  
 IF a is not an integer

   stop running code, and print response

      "a must be an integer"
  
  IF b is not an integer

    stop running code, and print response

     "b must be an integer"
  
 IF c is not an integer

   stop running code, and print response

      "b must be an integer"
  
 set r equal to the remainder of a divided by b

 set r2 equal to a

 set r3 equal to b

 set r4 equal to c

 IF r is equal to 0

    print response

     b

    ELSE conduct the following commands

     WHILE r3 does not equal 0

       set r1 equal to the remainder of r2 divided by r3

        set r2 to r3

       set r3 to r1

      IF r2 is greater than or equal to r4

        print the greatest common divisor of r2 and r4 in that order

     IF r4 is greater than r2

        print the greatest common divisor of r4 and r2 in that order

“Flowchart 2”

This program will allow the user to deterine whether an integer is a prime number

IF x is not an integer

    stop running code, and print response

      "input must be an integer greater than 1"

IF x is less than or equal to 1

    stop running code, and print response

      "input must be an integer greater than 1"
  
set sq equal to the square root of x rounded to the nearest whole number

IF x is equal to 2

 print "TRUE"

 ELSE IF any number from 2 to sq divided into x has no remainder

   print "False

   ELSE

     print "TRUE"

“Flowchart 3”

This program will allow the user to deterine which factors of an integer are prime

IF x is not an integer

   stop running code, and print response

      "input must be an integer greater than 1"

IF x is less than or equal to 1

   stop running code, and print response

     "input must be an integer greater than 1"

FOR every value i from 2 to the input value x

  IF the value i divides evenly into the input value x

    IF those values of i are determined to be prime numbers

     then print those values of i as a vector
